\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While Ehrenfest dynamics conserves the total energy of the quantum subsystem
 together with the EM field, our proposed extra +R relaxation changes the
 energy of the quantum subsystem by an additional amount:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{dU_{s}}{dt}=\text{Tr}\left\{ \widehat{H}_{s}{\cal L}_{R}\widehat{\rho}\right\} =-\Omega k_{R}\rho_{11}.
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Thus, during a time step 
\begin_inset Formula $dt$
\end_inset

, the change in energy for the radiation field is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\delta U_{R}=\Omega k_{R}\rho_{11}dt.\label{eq:EnergyChange}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

For the Ehrenfest+R approach to enforce the energy conservation, this energy
 loss must flow into the EM field in the form of light emission.
 In other words, we must rescale the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{E}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{B}$
\end_inset

